# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.example — committed; copy to .env and fill in your real values.
# .env is gitignored; never commit it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This package's email-integration tests need SMTP (send) + IMAP (receive)
# credentials. Tests automatically skip when these values are unset, so
# leaving them blank is fine for unit-only runs.
#
# Quick setup:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # then fill in the five variables below
#   npx playwright test                              # unit tests + email tests
#   npx playwright test --grep 'Email Integration'   # email tests only
#
# CI: add the same variables as repository secrets under
#   Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# in the GitHub repo, then reference them from your workflow as
# `${{ secrets.SENDER_EMAIL }}` etc.
#
# Security:
#   - NEVER commit `.env` or `.env.*.local` — they are in `.gitignore`.
#   - Use application-specific passwords, not your main account password.
#   - Rotate credentials periodically.


# ── Sender (SMTP) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by send-side tests. The current convention is a SendinBlue / Brevo
# SMTP relay; any SMTP host works as long as it accepts password auth.
#
# SendinBlue / Brevo setup:
#   1. Sign up at https://www.brevo.com/ (formerly SendinBlue).
#   2. Parameters & SMTP → SMTP, generate your API key.
#   3. Host: smtp-relay.brevo.com  (older accounts: smtp-relay.sendinblue.com)
SENDER_EMAIL=your-sender@example.com
SENDER_PASSWORD=your-sender-application-password
SENDER_SMTP_HOST=smtp-relay.sendinblue.com


# ── Receiver (IMAP) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by receive-side tests. Any IMAP-capable inbox works.
#
# Gmail setup:
#   1. Enable 2-Step Verification on the Google account.
#   2. Generate an App Password (Account → Security → App passwords).
#   3. Use the app password (not your Google password) in RECEIVER_PASSWORD.
#   4. IMAP host: imap.gmail.com:993 (the client defaults to this).
RECEIVER_EMAIL=your-receiver@example.com
RECEIVER_PASSWORD=your-receiver-application-password
